HEADWORD: Alquifou
<hw>Al"qui*fou</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Equiv. to
<ets>arquifoux</ets>, F. <ets>alquifoux</ets>, Sp.
<ets>alquif⟦oacute⟧l</ets>, fr. the same Arabic word as
<ets>alcohol</ets>. See <er>Alcohol</er>.]</ety> <def>A lead ore found
in Cornwall, England, and used by potters to give a green glaze to their
wares; potter's ore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

